" of it), but now |TS| needs to know what to proxy. This is achieved by "
"writing remap rules, which make use of the core :ref:`conf-remap-plugin`."
" For our Getting Started guide's |AW| example scenario, we have very "
"simple needs and want little more than to proxy all requests to our "
"single origin server. This is accomplished with the following rule added "
