# 9475139411a74abb8c80f6da45a4353e
#: ../../getting-started/index.en.rst:289
msgid ""
"It is worth pausing at this point to note that in a reverse proxying "
"scenario, it is |TS| itself which should be responding to HTTP requests "
"made to your public domain. While you first configure and evaluate "
"whether |TS| will meet your needs, your origin server will continue to "
"reside at the public-facing domain name on the default ports, should you "
"move your |TS| configuration into production your DNS records for the "
"domain(s) you wish to proxy and cache should resolve to the host(s) "
"running |TS| (in the event that you run it on a separate host from your "
"origin). Your origin should be accessible at a different address (or bind"
" to different ports if you are running both your origin service and |TS| "
"on the same host) and should no longer receive requests sent to the "
"primary domain on its default ports."
